org.fosstrak.reader.rprm.core
Class TagSelector

java.lang.Object
  org.fosstrak.reader.rprm.core.TagSelector

public final class TagSelector
extends java.lang.Object

A TagSelector is a non-mutable object that can exist as a member of a Source object (i.e., TagSelector objects are added and removed from a Source object). A Source object can contain zero or more TagSelector objects. It contains all information used for tag filtering.

Author:
Markus Vitalini

                                 TagField tagField,

                                 boolean inclusive,
                                 ReaderDevice readerDevice)
                          throws ReaderProtocolException
A static method to create a tag selector object with the given name. If a tag selector object with the same name exists, an exception ("ERROR_OBJECT_EXISTS") is thrown.

Parameters:
name - The name of the tagselector
tagField - The tag field of the dataselector
filterValue - The filter value
filterMask - The filter mask
inclusive - The inclusive flag
readerDevice - The instance of the reader device this tagselector belongs to
Returns:
The instance of the created tagselector
Throws:
ReaderProtocolException - "ERROR_OBJECT_EXISTS"
